We've got a great day planned,
a lot of deep technical content

00:01:14.570 --> 00:01:23.990
about programming for iOS 7.

00:01:24.340 --> 00:01:30.510
So before I get into sort of the
main content of this kickoff,

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:34.440
I wanted to start with a couple of
significant milestones of things that

00:01:34.440 --> 00:01:38.490
we've done over the last year that
address and respond to the feedback

00:01:38.490 --> 00:01:40.520
that we've heard from so many of you.

00:01:40.540 --> 00:01:46.320
So we recently announced that we've
shipped over 700 million iOS devices,

00:01:46.390 --> 00:01:51.290
which is a lot of devices for your apps,
and it's an enormous audience

00:01:51.290 --> 00:01:53.220
for you as a developer.

00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:58.590
And that includes the 9 million
new iPhones that shipped in the

00:01:58.590 --> 00:02:03.230
record-breaking 9 million devices
that were shipped in the first

00:02:03.280 --> 00:02:05.950
three days when these went on sale.

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:09.030
So some pretty incredible
sales numbers there.

00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:12.340
And obviously all these
devices shipped with iOS 7,

00:02:12.410 --> 00:02:17.040
but since iOS 7 updating is so easy,
more than 200 million of these

00:02:17.100 --> 00:02:21.390
700 million devices were updated
to iOS 7 in the first weekend

00:02:21.390 --> 00:02:23.660
in which iOS 7 was available.

00:02:24.250 --> 00:02:27.430
So that was a huge start,
a real fast start for us.

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:32.480
We were really excited with it,
and it's the fastest software

00:02:32.480 --> 00:02:37.410
upgrade in the history of iOS,
and it shows that iOS 7 is the

00:02:37.410 --> 00:02:40.340
most popular iOS update so far.

00:02:40.340 --> 00:02:44.300
And it's so popular, in fact,
that as of just the other day,

00:02:44.300 --> 00:02:48.350
we've got stats that show that
we have 74% of the installed

00:02:48.350 --> 00:02:50.310
base is running iOS 7.

00:02:50.320 --> 00:02:54.080
That's pretty much two-thirds
of all iOS devices.

00:02:54.200 --> 00:02:55.110
We're running iOS 7.

00:02:55.120 --> 00:03:00.660
And so clearly, this is a huge ramp-up to
the new operating system,

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:03.180
and clearly customers
love having the latest,

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:06.670
greatest software running on the latest,
greatest hardware.

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:12.330
And so you definitely want to be
there with your apps on iOS 7.

00:03:12.340 --> 00:03:16.940
Now, if you need to run on iOS 6 as well,
then you can, you know,

00:03:16.950 --> 00:03:22.580
obviously consider supporting adding
legacy support for those customers.

00:03:22.580 --> 00:03:26.930
But today... Is all about iOS 7,
and we want to teach you how to

00:03:26.930 --> 00:03:30.170
take advantage of everything that
is on this release because that's

00:03:30.170 --> 00:03:32.020
where so many of our customers are.

00:03:33.940 --> 00:03:36.680
Now, we've listened to your
feedback over the last year,

00:03:36.680 --> 00:03:38.800
and we've done a bunch of things for you.

00:03:38.830 --> 00:03:41.300
And I wanted to talk
about a few of these.

00:03:41.430 --> 00:03:44.500
First is we announced App Transfer.

00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:47.680
And this lets you move your
app from one team to another.

00:03:47.740 --> 00:03:50.690
For example, if you sell your app or
your company gets acquired,

00:03:50.810 --> 00:03:53.100
this is a big request from
the developer community.

00:03:53.150 --> 00:03:56.660
And this is now available for you.

00:03:56.690 --> 00:03:59.420
And recently,
over-the-air download limits were raised

00:03:59.420 --> 00:04:01.880
from 50 megabytes to 100 megabytes.

00:04:01.900 --> 00:04:05.010
And this makes it even easier
for people to get your apps,

00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:07.720
even if they're not connected to Wi-Fi.

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:12.600
So as you move to universal binary,
as you add support for Retina Display,

00:04:12.610 --> 00:04:16.360
as you add all kinds of new
capabilities to your apps,

00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:17.860
they've gotten bigger
and bigger over time.

00:04:17.900 --> 00:04:20.170
And so this is a pretty big deal.

