00:08:27.470 --> 00:08:30.280
our attention to the present.

00:08:30.330 --> 00:08:35.920
You know, 2013 was a busy year for us,
and we got a lot of stuff done,

00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:40.180
and it was a really important
year for several reasons.

00:08:40.230 --> 00:08:46.520
We saw primarily a fundamental
evolution in the iOS platform in 2013,

00:08:46.540 --> 00:08:51.800
and it started with the
introduction of iOS 7 at WWDC.

00:08:52.130 --> 00:08:56.190
iOS 7, as you know,
is the next generation of iOS,

00:08:56.250 --> 00:09:00.240
and it's the most significant
update to iOS since 2007.

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:06.450
You know, we're 2013 right now,
and it's hard to believe that iOS 7 is,

00:09:06.450 --> 00:09:09.850
you know, six or seven years old,
eight years old.

00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:12.320
I mean,
it seems like time has just flown.

00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:16.400
I mean, I've been at Apple for 14 years,
and I remember the day that iOS,

00:09:16.400 --> 00:09:18.680
you know, came out,
that the iPhone was introduced.

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:23.040
And since then, we've had, you know,
six major releases of iOS.

00:09:23.040 --> 00:09:25.410
Now we've got the seventh,
and it is the most

00:09:25.550 --> 00:09:27.430
significant release we've had.

00:09:27.460 --> 00:09:30.480
And as I mentioned before,
we've got hundreds of millions

00:09:30.520 --> 00:09:34.360
of customers on board with iOS 7
running on their devices already.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:43.100
And as you know,
iOS 7 has got this great new

00:09:43.100 --> 00:09:43.980
user experience that focuses
on people's content and brings

00:09:44.020 --> 00:09:49.410
a new level of physical realism
to the overall user experience.

00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:53.740
And we're going to get into this in a
lot more detail in a session following

00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:56.110
this one for user interface design.

00:09:56.210 --> 00:09:59.810
But iOS 7 brings, you know,
motion effects that

00:09:59.870 --> 00:10:01.580
give a sense of depth.

00:10:01.680 --> 00:10:05.400
It brings text that's far
more legible and dynamic.

00:10:05.470 --> 00:10:08.790
And there's a lot more-- there's
new gestures and new capabilities.

00:10:08.800 --> 00:10:12.000
So the overall user experience of
iOS 7 has changed pretty dramatically

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:13.940
from what was there before.

00:10:14.020 --> 00:10:17.120
And we're seeing a lot of apps
already that have been redesigned

00:10:17.120 --> 00:10:20.360
to take advantage of the new
user interface of iOS 7 and to

00:10:20.490 --> 00:10:22.380
fit into this new environment.

00:10:22.410 --> 00:10:25.340
And I want to show you
a couple of examples.

00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:28.880
Here's an exciting version
of--here's a new app called

00:10:29.050 --> 00:10:31.100
Sky Guide from 5th Star Labs.

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:36.300
And this is a stargazing app,
and they introduced-- you know,

00:10:36.300 --> 00:10:40.410
they worked on the UI for iOS
7 and introduced translucency,

00:10:40.440 --> 00:10:42.600
parallax, and dynamic type.

00:10:42.700 --> 00:10:45.100
So these are some initial
things that they've done,

00:10:45.100 --> 00:10:49.200
but the effect already on the
app has been pretty profound.

00:10:49.670 --> 00:10:51.600
Zite, one of my favorite apps.

00:10:51.600 --> 00:10:55.520
It's an intelligent magazine helping
you to discover interesting things,

00:10:55.620 --> 00:10:58.080
articles that are out on the
net based on your interests.

00:10:58.130 --> 00:11:03.660
And they completely revamped the
UI and looked to clean up their design,

00:11:03.660 --> 00:11:07.120
improve the legibility of their content.

00:11:07.120 --> 00:11:09.910
They enlarged photos
and went edge to edge.

00:11:09.910 --> 00:11:13.400
They added some subtle motion effects
as you're scrolling through the content.

00:11:13.400 --> 00:11:15.980
And they added support
for iOS 7 gestures.

00:11:16.600 --> 00:11:20.000
So again, some preliminary steps
for this developer,

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:23.270
but the result is a pretty
dramatic change to the app as

00:11:23.270 --> 00:11:25.520
compared to the iOS 6 version.

00:11:27.190 --> 00:11:29.140
Here's another app called Just.me.

00:11:29.140 --> 00:11:32.590
It's a sharing app that
offers the best of texting,

00:11:32.690 --> 00:11:35.330
email, and networking all in one app.

00:11:35.410 --> 00:11:39.770
And they worked hard to remove all
of the extra adornments that they

00:11:39.770 --> 00:11:44.170
had on screen and to give space to
the content that really mattered,

00:11:44.170 --> 00:11:48.110
which was the content that
users are producing in the app.

00:11:48.560 --> 00:11:51.930
They focused on bigger text,
edge-to-edge photos,

00:11:51.930 --> 00:11:53.820
and minimal distractions.

00:11:53.820 --> 00:11:56.590
And the result is
something that's pretty,

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:58.040
pretty gorgeous.

00:11:59.940 --> 00:12:00.870
Here's Evernote.

00:12:00.910 --> 00:12:04.340
It won an Apple Design Award this
past year at WWDC.

00:12:04.340 --> 00:12:09.200
And on the left is the iOS 6 version
that won an Apple Design Award,

00:12:09.200 --> 00:12:12.310
along with their Mac app and
their Safari extension and all

00:12:12.310 --> 00:12:15.540
the stuff they were doing on
the various Apple platforms.

00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:17.860
And on the right side,
you've got the current

00:12:17.860 --> 00:12:19.260
shipping iOS 7 version.

00:12:19.260 --> 00:12:23.980
And Evernote chose to
reinvent the app around iOS 7.

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:29.860
So they stopped, they looked at iOS 7,
and they decided to just redo

00:12:29.890 --> 00:12:34.760
the entire experience as if
it was their first version.

00:12:34.760 --> 00:12:38.320
And that meant that they could
throw out some old ideas,

00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:42.790
some old ways of thinking about things,
and restructure the content,

00:12:42.930 --> 00:12:45.620
lay it out differently,
and really optimize it.

00:12:45.720 --> 00:12:46.340
And they did that, and they did that,
and they did that, and they did that,

00:12:46.370 --> 00:12:46.980
and they did that, and they did that,
and they did that, and they did that,

00:12:46.980 --> 00:12:47.840
and they did that, and they did that,
and they did that.

00:12:47.840 --> 00:12:51.230
And so as part of the redesign,
they added translucency

00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:52.660
and depth with UIKit.

00:12:52.660 --> 00:12:55.400
They added multitasking background sync.

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:57.710
They did AirDrop for sharing of notes.

00:12:57.870 --> 00:13:02.310
And they did TextKit support for
better text management and layout.

00:13:02.340 --> 00:13:06.610
And pretty dramatic change
from where they were before.

00:13:08.720 --> 00:13:12.500
Here's American Airlines with a
completely redesigned app for iOS 7.

00:13:12.520 --> 00:13:15.920
On the left is their
previous iOS 6 version,

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:18.640
and on the right is
their new iOS 7 version.

00:13:18.640 --> 00:13:23.070
And the goal that they had was to
improve legibility and introduce

00:13:23.070 --> 00:13:24.910
a much stronger design aesthetic.

00:13:24.920 --> 00:13:32.500
And the design that they did for iOS
7 brings in translucency and depth.

00:13:32.620 --> 00:13:34.860
It's a much cleaner design.

00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:38.220
It focuses on the content
that you really care about,

00:13:38.350 --> 00:13:42.540
and so there's greater legibility for
the things that matter most to you.

00:13:42.850 --> 00:13:45.600
And the result is pretty dramatic.

00:13:49.520 --> 00:13:51.830
And so these are five examples
of apps that have been

00:13:51.970 --> 00:13:57.110
completely redesigned for iOS 7,
but there are so many more.

00:13:58.130 --> 00:14:02.200
These are a bunch of apps that have
done a ton of work to revamp for iOS 7.

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:07.130
